  "title": "Automation Tester (Tosca)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Software Automation Tester (Tricentis Tosca) - 1 year Contract – Singapore</strong></p>\n<p>We are looking for an <strong>Automation Tester </strong>with at least 2 years of hands-on experience in <strong>Tricentis Tosca.</strong></p>\n<p>The ideal candidate will be responsible for designing, developing, and executing <strong>automated test scripts</strong> to validate the quality and performance of <strong>desktop, web</strong>, and <strong>mobile applications</strong>. This role requires proficiency in <strong>Tosca Test Automation</strong> and the ability to collaborate effectively with cross-functional teams.</p>\n<p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Develop, maintain, and optimize automated test scripts for <strong>desktop</strong>, <strong>web</strong>, and <strong>mobile platforms</strong> using <strong>Tricentis Tosca</strong>, and other test automation tools.</li>\n  <li>Create <strong>modular</strong>, <strong>reusable test scripts</strong> to improve the <strong>efficiency</strong> and speed of the testing process.</li>\n  <li>Automate <strong>functional tests</strong>, <strong>regression tests</strong>, <strong>integration tests</strong>, and <strong>smoke tests</strong>, leveraging a <strong>model-based testing approach</strong>.</li>\n  <li>Work closely with developers and business analysts to define <strong>testing requirements</strong> and ensure complete <strong>test coverage</strong> of application features.</li>\n  <li>Design and execute detailed <strong>automated test cases</strong>, track results, and report findings using test management tools such as <strong>JIRA</strong> and <strong>TestRail</strong>.</li>\n  <li>Analyze test results, identify defects, and ensure timely reporting and resolution.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Qualifications:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>2+ years of experience in <strong>Tricentis Tosca.</strong></li>\n  <li>Strong experience with <strong>test management tools</strong> like <strong>JIRA</strong>, <strong>TestRail</strong>, or equivalents.</li>\n  <li>Proven ability to develop and maintain automated test scripts for various platforms (<strong>desktop</strong>, <strong>web</strong>, <strong>mobile</strong>).</li>\n  <li>Familiarity with <strong>Agile</strong> or <strong>Scrum</strong> methodologies.</li>\n  <li>Experience testing applications across multiple platforms, including <strong>mobile</strong> and <strong>web</strong>.</li>\n  <li>Basic knowledge of programming or scripting languages commonly used in test automation (e.g., <strong>Java</strong>, <strong>Python</strong>, <strong>JavaScript</strong>).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Why Join Us?</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Work on cutting-edge applications in a dynamic environment.</li>\n  <li>Opportunities for professional growth and skill development.</li>\n  <li>Competitive salary and benefits package.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>This is a 1 year contract to start, renewable and convertible to permanent</p>",
